# 3. Technology Stack
- **Documentation Format**: Markdown (.md)
- **Version Control**: Git
- **Build System**: Custom `!build` command
- **Architecture Style**: Modular, cross-referenced knowledge base
- **Content Structure**: 8-section template per file (Title & Summary, Problem Statement, Solution, When to Use, Tradeoffs, Implementation Example, Anti-Pattern, Related Patterns)

# 4. Data Flows
- **Content Creation Flow**: Phase 1 (Foundation, Week 1) → Phase 2 (Core Patterns, Week 2-3) → Phase 3 (Engineering, Week 4-5) → Phase 4 (Infrastructure, Week 6-7) → Phase 5 (DevOps & Review, Week 8)
- **Knowledge Discovery Flow**: User reads category → accesses individual pattern files → follows cross-references to related paradigms and anti-patterns → progressively advances from basic to advanced concepts
- **Testing Pyramid Distribution**: 70% Unit Tests → 20% Integration Tests → 10% End-to-End Tests
- **Pattern Reference Flow**: Each pattern independently accessible but linked to related concepts enabling non-linear exploration while maintaining logical reading order through sequential numbering

