# 2. Design Patterns

## Architectural Patterns

**Modular Knowledge Base Pattern**
- Each pattern exists as an independent markdown file
- Categories provide logical grouping and navigation
- Cross-references enable knowledge discovery and connection

**Progressive Disclosure Pattern**
- Basic concepts documented first (System Design, Design Patterns)
- Advanced concepts follow (Distributed Systems, Infrastructure)
- Users can progressively advance through categories

**Context-First Pattern**
- Every pattern includes "When to Use" section
- Tradeoffs explicitly documented for informed decisions
- Problem statement precedes solution for context

## Content Organization Patterns

**8-Section Template Pattern**
- Consistent structure across all 55 content files
- Title & Summary → Problem → Solution → When → Tradeoffs → Example → Anti-Pattern → Related
- Enables predictable navigation and comparison

**Cross-Referencing Pattern**
- Patterns link to related paradigms
- Anti-patterns reference their correct pattern counterparts
- Related patterns section enables knowledge graph navigation

## System Design Patterns

**Testing Pyramid Distribution**
- 70% Unit Tests (Many, Fast, Cheap)
- 20% Integration Tests (Some, Medium Speed)
- 10% End-to-End Tests (Few, Slow, Expensive)

**Sequential Numbering Pattern**
- Categories numbered 01-11 for logical ordering
- Files within categories numbered sequentially
- Enables predictable file discovery and reading order

