## Build Command

```bash
# Custom build command for knowledge base validation
!build

# This command should:
# 1. Validate all 57 files exist (2 root + 55 content)
# 2. Verify each content file has 8 sections
# 3. Check cross-references are valid
# 4. Generate table of contents
# 5. Output build status and any errors
```

## Git Commands

```bash
# Initial commit after structure creation
git add .
git commit -m "Initial knowledge base structure with 57 files"

# Phase commits following 8-week timeline
git commit -m "Phase 1: Foundation - System-Design category complete"
git commit -m "Phase 2: Core Patterns - Design Patterns, Paradigms, Best Practices"
git commit -m "Phase 3: Engineering - Safety, Testing, Distributed Systems"
git commit -m "Phase 4: Infrastructure - Database, Infrastructure, Observability"
git commit -m "Phase 5: DevOps & Review - Complete knowledge base"
```

